  "instructions": [
    "Cut the beef into thin strips.",
    "Finely chop garlic, shallots, and ginger.",
    "In a wok or large frying pan, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat.",
    "Add chopped garlic, shallots, and ginger to the heated oil. Stir-fry for about 2 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add beef strips, soy sauce, oyster sauce, chili paste (if using), tomato paste, water/broth, and salt/pepper to taste. Stir well to coat the beef with the sauce mixture.",
    "Stir frequently for about 5-7 minutes until the beef is cooked through and the sauce has thickened slightly.",
